  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense under legislation in most countries. It is typically addressed in criminal codes or specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, making it appear to come from a legitimate source. Many jurisdictions have strict laws and penalties for money laundering, including:\n\n1. Criminal prosecution\n2. Substantial fines\n3. Asset seizure\n4. Potential imprisonment\n\nThe specific details and severity of money laundering laws can vary between countries, but it is generally treated as a serious criminal offense.",
